---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const lang = 'en';
---

<BaseLayout title="Manifesto | Ayamatma" description="Protocols of Inquiry (Vicāra-Niyama) — the rules of engagement for rigorous Vedāntic inquiry." lang={lang}>
  <section class="section stack">
    <h1 class="section-title">Vicāra-Niyama</h1>
    <p class="muted">Protocols of Inquiry</p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="prose manifesto-intro">
      <p class="lead">We are not a sect. We are not a church. We are a research collective.</p>
      <p>
        To maintain the integrity of <em>Ayamatma</em>, all content, dialogue, and inquiry on this platform
        adhere to the following <strong>Five Protocols</strong>. These guardrails ensure that our exploration
        of Vedānta remains intellectually honest, scientifically literate, and experientially grounded.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section protocol">
    <div class="protocol-header">
      <span class="protocol-number">I</span>
      <div>
        <h2 class="protocol-title">The Protocol of Authority</h2>
        <p class="protocol-sanskrit">Pramāṇa-Vicāra</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="protocol-principle">Truth is found in evidence, not in hierarchy.</p>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        <strong>Rejection of Personality Cults:</strong> We respect the <em>Guru-shishya paramparā</em> (lineage)
        as a pedagogical necessity, not a power structure. On this platform, an argument's validity depends
        entirely on its logic (<em>yukti</em>) and scriptural alignment (<em>śāstra</em>), never on the
        "spiritual status" of the speaker.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Primary Sources Over Interpretation:</strong> We prioritize the source texts (Upaniṣads,
        Brahma Sūtra, Bhagavad Gītā) over modern neo-Vedantic interpretations. When distinct commentators
        (Śaṅkara, Rāmānuja, Madhva) disagree, we analyze the divergence philologically and philosophically,
        rather than declaring one "heretical."
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>The Right to Dissent:</strong> Disagreement is not disrespect; it is the fuel of
        <em>Manana</em> (reflection). If a teaching cannot withstand the heat of questioning,
        it is not knowledge—it is dogma.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section protocol">
    <div class="protocol-header">
      <span class="protocol-number">II</span>
      <div>
        <h2 class="protocol-title">The Protocol of Science</h2>
        <p class="protocol-sanskrit">Vijñāna-Maryādā</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="protocol-principle">Science and Vedānta illuminate different domains; we do not blur them for comfort.</p>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        <strong>No Quantum Mysticism:</strong> We strictly forbid the misuse of scientific terminology
        to lend false credibility to metaphysical claims. Quantum mechanics is a mathematical model of
        physical probability; it is not a synonym for <em>Māyā</em> or <em>Brahman</em>.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Models vs. Reality:</strong> We use scientific concepts (thermodynamics, systems theory,
        neuroplasticity) as <strong>analogies</strong> (<em>dṛṣṭānta</em>) to help the modern mind grasp
        abstract concepts. We acknowledge that these are pedagogical tools, not empirical proofs of the Self.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Falsifiability:</strong> Where Vedānta makes empirical claims about the physical world
        (cosmology, physiology), we defer to modern scientific consensus. Where Vedānta speaks of the
        Subject (<em>Dṛk</em>), science must pause, as the observer cannot be the observed.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section protocol">
    <div class="protocol-header">
      <span class="protocol-number">III</span>
      <div>
        <h2 class="protocol-title">The Protocol of Language</h2>
        <p class="protocol-sanskrit">Śabda-Śuddhi</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="protocol-principle">Precision in language is the prerequisite for clarity in thought.</p>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        <strong>Sanskrit Integrity:</strong> We reject the "digestible" translation if it destroys meaning.
        We do not translate <em>Ātman</em> merely as "Soul" or <em>Dharma</em> as "Religion." We use the
        original Sanskrit terms, define them contextually, and demand the user engage with the nuance.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Etymological Transparency:</strong> We analyze terms based on their <em>dhātu</em> (root)
        and historical usage. We trace how a word like <em>Karma</em> evolves from "ritual action" in the
        Vedas to "moral causality" in the Gītā.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>No Word Salad:</strong> "Energy," "Vibration," and "Frequency" are banned unless used in
        their strict equations-based physics context.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section protocol">
    <div class="protocol-header">
      <span class="protocol-number">IV</span>
      <div>
        <h2 class="protocol-title">The Protocol of Argument</h2>
        <p class="protocol-sanskrit">Vāda-Nīti</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="protocol-principle">We engage to uncover truth, not to win debates.</p>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        <strong>The Steel Man Rule (Pūrvapakṣa):</strong> Before critiquing a view (whether Materialism,
        Buddhism, or Dualism), one must be able to state that view so well that its proponent would say,
        "Yes, that is exactly what I mean." We do not attack Straw Men.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Logical Consistency:</strong> Arguments must adhere to standard logical frameworks
        (Indian <em>Nyāya</em> or Western logic). Fallacies—ad hominem, circular reasoning, appeal to
        emotion—are grounds for dismissal.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Admit Uncertainty:</strong> If a question has no clear answer in text or experience,
        we say "We do not know." We do not fabricate certainty.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section protocol">
    <div class="protocol-header">
      <span class="protocol-number">V</span>
      <div>
        <h2 class="protocol-title">The Protocol of Experience</h2>
        <p class="protocol-sanskrit">Anubhava-Sūtra</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="protocol-principle">Map reading is not territory exploration.</p>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        <strong>Practice is Non-Negotiable:</strong> Intellectual understanding (<em>parokṣa jñāna</em>)
        is only the entry fee. We demand that inquiry moves toward <em>aparokṣa</em> (direct) verification.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Psychological Honesty:</strong> We distinguish between genuine spiritual insight and
        psychological escapism (spiritual bypassing). We advocate for addressing emotional and psychological
        shadow work alongside metaphysical inquiry.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>The End is Silence:</strong> All words, including these protocols, are part of <em>Māyā</em>.
        They are thorns used to remove a thorn. Once the job is done, both are discarded.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="quote-block">
      <p class="sanskrit">वादे वादे जायते तत्त्वबोधः</p>
      <p class="english">Through rigorous debate, the knowledge of truth arises.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .manifesto-intro .lead {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--accent-warm);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .protocol {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding-top: 2rem;
  }

  .protocol-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .protocol-number {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    font-weight: 300;
    line-height: 1;
    color: var(--accent-warm);
    opacity: 0.7;
    min-width: 2.5rem;
  }

  .protocol-title {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 1.35rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    margin: 0;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .protocol-sanskrit {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--accent-cool);
    margin: 0.25rem 0 0 0;
  }

  .protocol-principle {
    font-family: 'Fraunces', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem 0;
    padding-left: 3.75rem;
  }

  .protocol .prose {
    padding-left: 3.75rem;
  }

  .protocol .prose p {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .protocol .prose p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .protocol-header {
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.5rem;
    }

    .protocol-number {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }

    .protocol-principle,
    .protocol .prose {
      padding-left: 0;
    }
  }
</style>
